{
  "doc_id": "38593",
  "text": "Social media posts, and in particular Microposts collected from Twitter, have been found to contain useful information for many applications including disaster detection [CITATION_1] , seasonal mood level changes [CITATION_2] , tracking influenza rates [CITATION_3] , box-office revenue forecast [CITATION_4] , political elections [CITATION_5] , stock market prediction [CITATION_6] , etc. For instance, during the widespread protest in Egypt in 2013, Microposts were found to provide early warning signals of violent events; such events were reported much faster than traditional media sources [CITATION_7] . The real-time identification of such events could be extremely important to authorities and emergency professionals by allowing such parties to immediately respond.",
